<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=bdavis&Board=wizard&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View GreyBear_Orcburner (bdavis) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 "> | </font><a href="mailto:bdavis@peoplepublish.com" OnMouseOver="window.status='Send email to GreyBear_Orcburner.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Email</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hi all,<p>

I'm GreyBear, a 34 Wiz on Bristle. I've been lurking here for a while (as well as other places), but I've got an idea for a possible new EQ Casters Site and thought you all might have some good feedback to give.<p>

I've looked at and used most (if not all) of the Caster oriented boards araound, but I've noticed some familiar problems with them:<p>

1. Not a lot of really useful content specific to casters.<br>
2. Lots of duplication.<br>
3. A certain level of, well, staleness.<p>

I also think I *may* have a different approach, which may allow the creation of a new type of site paradigm.<p>

All of these sites are run by people or small groups who push content out at us readers. Some have better feedback than others, but all of the sites are managed by fiat. That is, what they post is what they like, or think is (important, cool, newsworthy - insert your adjective here).<p>

My idea is to reverse this a bit. In other words, I propose setting up a site that is run by it's readers. The content is managed and supplied by those who visit the site. I'm not going to go into detail here about how this is done, but basically it would be along the lines of a reverse SourceForge operation. Anyone who's willing to create an account could add content to the site, without prior permission or censorship. This leaves open the possibility of abuse, but I'm willing to bet that this won't be a major problem with a few security precautions and a healthy does of self policing.<p>

Why would I want to do this? Well, one thing I can think of right off that I always wanted and could never find was a specific guide on wizard solo levelling, with zone and MOB locations specific to each level or group of levels. How cool would it be for a newbie caster to be able to come and get this type of information? And with all of us in these forums who have that knowledge pooling it onto a site like this, it could be done in pretty short order.<p>

So, does this sound like something you all would like, and use, and contribute to? I can provide the servers. I can provide the connection. I can provide at least a good portion of the backend programming and administrative support. What I can't provide is the content. <p>

Comments? Suggestions?<p>

Thanks for listening... #8^D<hr>GreyBear Orcburner<br>
Wizard of Bristlebane<br>
-<br>
"...for you are crunchy, and good with ketchup..."</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
